    "Combined together, DRL has gotten rapid traction and is currently thriving with accomplishments mastering the complexity of MAPF by employing neural networks as function approximators (Arulkumaran et al. 2017; Gronauer and Diepold 2022).",
    "This section provides insights into DRL to help new researchers in this field in building a solid foundation.",
    "In the subsequent sections, we will delve into the strengths of DRL-based approaches in MAPF, the DRL-based MAPF framework, a variety of DRL algorithms, and multi-agent DRL algorithms.",
